Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C) Core tomatoes and slice ¼ inch (0.5 cm) off top. Scoop out seeds and juice to form a cavity. Chop tops and inside flesh. Set aside. Arrange tomatoes in prepared dish. Set aside. In a saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add garlic, onion and mushrooms. Sauté for 5 minutes or until soft. Add reserved chopped tomato, rice, basil, oregano and thyme. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Add salt and pepper, to taste. Spoon stuffing equally into tomato cavities. Sprinkle each with 1 tbsp (15 mL) of the Parmesan. Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts and tomatoes begin to soften. Serve immediately.